{
  "stem": "19198.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very little, but having been to Paris, I had learned there that the Statue of Liberty was a gift of the French people to the United States of America.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that had relatively little impact on the feelings that I had as the ship pulled into the harbor of New York.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, compared to the-- to being in the harbor of New York, even the Statue of Liberty was a relatively small matter.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had relatives on my mother's side, the members of the rather extensive David family, who met me and in whose home I spent the three days that we were scheduled to stay in New York.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think that most of them had either relatives or acquaintances in New York.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't recall any of them staying in a hotel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm quite sure that on one or two occasions we went to see some sight in New York together.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But most of the time, as far as I recall, we were on our own.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the-- my hosts were able to show me the ropes of get around in New York.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Was a big place.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the skyscrapers were real.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They weren't just pictures.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Frankly, I remember very little specifics about my-- that-- those three days in New York.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One thing that I became aware of was the-- how radical the difference in pronunciation was, of-- even though everybody spoke the same language.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I-- for instance, I recall my hostess, who was a first cousin of my mother's, calling her one son who was playing out in the streets, 'Boinie,' which of course I would have spelled B-O-I-N-I-E.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then I found out that it really was B-E-R-N-I-E, and I was staying in the Bronx.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
